### Timer-Based Events

You can create timer-based behaviors using the update event:

```javascript
// Create a timer system
const timers = {
  animation: { 
    duration: 5, 
    current: 0,
    active: true
  }
}

app.on('update', (dt) => {
  // Update timers
  Object.values(timers).forEach(timer => {
    if (timer.active) {
      timer.current += dt
      
      if (timer.current >= timer.duration) {
        // Timer completed
        timer.current = 0
        // Perform action or reset
      }
    }
  })
})
